\pard\f0\fs28 Subgen. {\b Acetosella} (Meissner) Rech. fil. Dioecious (very rarely polygamous). Slender perennials with acid taste. Valves seldom much longer than the nut, without tubercles. Leaves hastate or sagittate, sometimes with several pairs of basal lobes.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. R. acetosella} L., {\i Sp. Pl. }338 (1753) ({\i R. fascilobus} Klokov). Stems 5-75 cm, erect or ascending, branching at or above the middle. Leaves hastate; central lobe lanceolate or linear; basal lobes 2 (rarely 0) or 2-15 pairs. Inflorescence less leafy than the lower stem. Nut 0·8-1·5 mm, obtusely trigonous, adhering to (angiocarpous) or free from (gymnocarpous) the valves. {\i Calcifuge. Almost throughout Europe}. All except Bl, Rs(K); naturalized in Sb.
\par

\par

