\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. R. graminifolius} J.H. Rudolph ex Lamb.,{\i  Trans. Linn. Soc. London }{\b 10:} 264 (1811) ({\i R. angustissimus} Ledeb.). Stem usually procumbent. Leaves small, narrowly linear, obtuse; basal lobes indistinct or absent. Valves from slightly longer than to nearly twice as long as the nut. Nut c. 1·8 mm, longer than wide. 2n = 56.{\i  Arctic Europe, extending southwards to} 61°{\i  N. in N.W. Russia.} No Rs(N, C).
\par

